SUMMARY:ABCD Reads "The Age of Innocence" by Edith Wharton
DESCRIPTION:A Book Club\, Downtown (ABCD)\nABCD Reads "**[The Age of Innoc
 ence](https://www.torontopubliclibrary.ca/detail.jsp?Entt=RDM185033&R=1850
 33)**" by Edith Wharton\n[[RESULTS](https://opavote.com/results/5169317438
 291968) of the poll for this event]\n\n**:: ABOUT THE BOOK ::**\n"Winner o
 f the 1921 Pulitzer Prize\, The Age of Innocence is Edith Wharton’s mast
 erful portrait of desire and betrayal during the sumptuous Golden Age of O
 ld New York\, a time when society people “dreaded scandal more than dise
 ase.”\nThis is Newland Archer’s world as he prepares to marry the beau
 tiful but conventional May Welland. But when the mysterious Countess Ellen
  Olenska returns to New York after a disastrous marriage\, Archer falls de
 eply in love with her. Torn between duty and passion\, Archer struggles to
  make a decision that will either courageously define his life—or mercil
 essly destroy it." (from [Goodreads](https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/5
 3835.The_Age_of_Innocence))\n\n"Set in the 1870s\, the novel revolves arou
 nd Newland Archer\, a young lawyer from New York's high society\, who is e
 ngaged to the beautiful and conventional May Welland. His life takes a tur
 n when he meets May's cousin\, the Countess Ellen Olenska\, who has return
 ed from Europe after leaving her scandalous husband. Torn between his duty
  and passion\, Archer struggles with the constraints of the society he is 
 a part of. The book offers a vivid portrayal of the struggle between indiv
 idual desires and societal expectations in the upper-class New York societ
 y of the late 19th century." (from [The Greatest Books](https://thegreates
 tbooks.org/books/146))\n\n**:: ABOUT THE EVENT ::**\nYou are welcome to ar
 rive 30 minutes before the event and stay 30 minutes or longer afterward t
 o connect with other attendees outside the book talk.\n\nPlease ensure you
  have read the book before attending (though finishing any book is not a b
 arrier to participating\, as long as you don't mind spoilers).\n\nFirst-ti
 me attendees can join for free. If the event is full\, we maintain an unof
 ficial waitlist. Please send [Michael](https://www.meetup.com/members/5529
 5192/) a direct message for more information\, in either case.\n\nWe reque
 st a $3 contribution from regular attendees to help cover our monthly meet
 up costs.\n\n**:: ABOUT OUR NEXT BOOK ::**\nAt the end of each event\, we 
 will ask for nominees for our next book. If you have a good one in mind\, 
 please ensure it is between 200-400 pages long\, available from the Toront
 o Public Library\, and counts as contemporary literary fiction (though the
 se are not hard and fast rules). When enough nominees are collected\, Mich
 ael will send the members a direct message with a link where you can vote.
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.meetup.com/a-book-club-downtown-abcd/events/3128
 85146/
