SUMMARY:ABCD Reads "What We Can Know" by Ian McEwan
DESCRIPTION:A Book Club\, Downtown (ABCD)\nABCD Reads "**[What We Can Know
 ](https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/record/S234C4683360)**" by Ian McEwan.\
 n\n[[RESULTS](https://opavote.com/results/6276009911648256) of the poll fo
 r this event]\n\n**:: ABOUT THE BOOK ::**\n"A quest\, a literary thriller 
 and a love story\, *What We Can Know* spans the past\, present and future 
 to ask profound questions about who we are and where we are going.\n2014: 
 A great poem is read aloud and never heard again. For generations\, people
  speculate about its message\, but no copy has yet been found.\n2119: The 
 lowlands of the UK have been submerged by rising seas. Those who survive a
 re haunted by the richness of the world that has been lost.\nTom Metcalfe\
 , a scholar at the University of the South Downs\, part of Britain's remai
 ning archipelagos\, pores over the archives of the early twenty-first cent
 ury\, captivated by the freedoms and possibilities of human life at its ze
 nith.\nWhen he stumbles across a clue that may lead to the great lost poem
 \, revelations of entangled love and a brutal crime emerge\, destroying hi
 s assumptions about a story he thought he knew intimately.\n*What We Can K
 now* is a masterpiece that reclaims the present from our sense of looming 
 catastrophe\, and imagines a future world where all is not quite lost." (f
 rom [Goodreads](https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/223854881-what-we-can-
 know))\n\n"A love story about both people and the words they leave behind\
 , a literary detective story which reclaims the present from our sense of 
 looming catastrophe and imagines a future world where all is not quite los
 t." (from [Bookmarks.reviews](https://bookmarks.reviews/reviews/what-we-ca
 n-know/))\n\n**:: ABOUT THE EVENT ::**\nYou are welcome to arrive 30 minut
 es before the event and stay 30 minutes or longer afterward to connect wit
 h other attendees outside the book talk.\n\nPlease ensure you have read th
 e book before attending (though finishing any book is not a barrier to par
 ticipating\, as long as you don't mind spoilers).\n\nFirst-time attendees 
 can join for free. If the event is full\, we maintain an unofficial waitli
 st. Please send [Michael](https://www.meetup.com/members/55295192/) a dire
 ct message for more information\, in either case.\n\nWe request a $3 contr
 ibution from regular attendees to help cover our monthly meetup costs.\n\n
 **:: ABOUT OUR NEXT BOOK ::**\nAt the end of each event\, we will ask for 
 nominees for our next book. If you have a good one in mind\, please ensure
  it is between 200-400 pages long\, available from the Toronto Public Libr
 ary\, and counts as contemporary literary fiction (though these are not ha
 rd and fast rules). When enough nominees are collected\, Michael will send
  the members a direct message with a link where you can vote.
